column1: # The figures in three 1850s sheets have a lot of duplication for 1853 onwards.
# It looks like a replacement gauge (page 219) may have come in to operation in 1853 ?
# Figures for 1850-1852 are taken from page 217, for 1853 onwards from page 219. The figures on Page 218 are not used.
# The gauge operated at several early sites in Scarborough, including Belle Vue(TA037882), The Museum (TA043883) and King Street (TA044886).
